article.headline: Andino, UMES beat Central Penn 87-74 to snap 8-game skid
article.linkText: Andino, UMES beat Central Penn 87-74 to snap 8-game skid
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. -- Ryan Andino hit six 3-pointers and finished with 20 points, Logan McIntosh scored 16 on 6-of-8 shooting and Maryland-Eastern Shore beat Central Penn 87-74 on Monday night to snap an eight-game skid dating to last season. Thomas Rivera and Bakari Copeland added 13 points apiece for the Hawks. UMES (1-7) trailed 17-9 about six minutes in, but took a 22-21 lead on a 3 by Andino with 9:30 left in the half and a layup by McIntosh gave the Hawks the lead for good and sparked a 16-5 run that made it 42-32 at halftime. Central Penn, a member of the United States Collegiate Athletic Association, trailed by double figures throughout the second half. Tyree Tucker hit five 3s and scored 20 points, and Tyrie Orosco added 18 points for the Knights, who shot just 35.9 percent and committed 26 turnovers.
